Option 1: GATK Best Practices
Tools:
Trimmomatic
FastQC
PicardTools
GATK
TRAMS

Workflow:
0) download/setup 
 a) reference genome (fasta) 
 b) reference GBK
 c) dbSNP (or blank.vcf if none)

1) Trimmomatic
#assuming Truseq3 adapters, single ended, adapt as needed
ILLUMINACLIP:TruSeq3-SE:2:30:10 LEADING:3 TRAILING:3 MINLEN:75

2)Fastqc

3)BWA mem to reference genome (using read groups)

4) PICARDTOOLS
 a) SortSAM
 b) MarkDuplicates
 c) BuildBamIndex

5) GATK
 a) RealignerTargetCreator
 b) IndelRealigner
 c) BaseRecalibrator -o prelimTable
 d) BaseRecalibrator -BQSR -o post_proc
 e) PrintReads 

6) Picardtools
 a) BuildBamIndex

7) GATK 
 a) HaplotypeCaller
#if multiple samples:
 b) CombineGVCFs
 c) GenotypeGVCFs
 d) VariantAnnotator
 e) VariantEval
 f) VariantsToTable

8) TRAMS (plus custom script)
 a) custom perl vcf2trams.pl (makes trams compatable file)
 b) TRAMS.py 

